annotation.TEXT: I'm expecting to lose Yoshi here, though...
What the? Hey, what's Yoshi doing in here? He shouldn't have been able to come in here with me! Is it because I started from midpoint?
Alright, Wendy. Now, it's just me and you... and your dummies.

Well, I guess this is a good time to point out something odd here: Check out my reserve item. Yeah, its graphics are glitched out here! (And if I had a mushroom, it would look like a podoboo, which was visible in my battle against Lemmy in the third castle.)
Nuts. Doesn't look like Ninji is edible.
...And again!
Whoa, watch out! Chuck coming through!
Woo, close call in a non-important situation. (If I got hit there, I'm sure I could've easily retrieved Yoshi with no problem.)
I don't know. It didn't make any platforms over the munchers, which is kind of what I was expecting...
Oh, man. This jump looks tricky...

Hello, and welcome back to Choco Ghost House! Now, it dawned on me what the P-switch in this level is probably for, just after I uploaded the previous episode. Take a wild guess as to what the P-switch here will do!
Huh. The Vanilla Dome map music is still playing for some reason. Well, I wonder what the next level will be, but that'll have to wait until next time!
Gah! That was me being an idiot. Well, are they burnable?
Okay, now to magically go back in time to just before I entered the boss room!
Oh, but I should take out the diagonal podoboo with a fireball since I can. That'll give me one less thing to worry about.
And, judging by where the screen stopped scrolling, I'm expecting the victory music to be cutoff.
Yep, it created a platform here, allowing me to open this block! But, it just contains a flower, which I don't need.
Oh, thank you parakoopa that wasn't there in the original game!
Yep, called it! Alright, so up next is the castle! (Aw, and it was feeling like I had just begun world 6...)
Gotcha! And with that, world 6 is now complete!
I wonder why the hit detection is so out of whack like that?
Umm... This jump looks really tough. I hope a low jump (Down+A) works here!
Well, there's the problem-- Mario's been using a way outdated version of Internet Explorer!
Wait, what? The cape can knock back the little guys, but it doesn't kill or even stun them! That's rather unusual!
So, is it Wendy?
Okay, let's try this again, but not fry Wendy this time!
Alright, I guess Chuck isn't concerned with fighting me. I'm fine with that. Now, what's this P-switch do?
What the? Were there two Dino-Torches overlapping there, or did my first shot hit one that was off screen?

Yep, that totally worked! But all I get is a simple mushroom. I was kind of hoping for the cape... (In the original game, that block is either a yellow ! block or a green ! block, depending on which particular nearly identical sublevel you're in.)
Okay, now to crash the game by switching to my cape while Mario is in his fireball shooting animation!
Push!
D'oh! I hit the spikes (which I guess Yoshi can't stand here), and then Yoshi clipped through the floor! That stinks...
Yeah, it's kind of like when Yoshi eats a boss in the original (using a hack or glitch that allows Yoshi into a boss room). So, now I guess I'm stuck.
That was perfect for the job, because any higher jump would've hit that pencil, and I think that gap would be a bit too wide to just run across!
Oh, man. That turn block totally has something in it, but there's nothing to stand on below it.
Well, can I enter the door with him? Yes, I can!
So, what if I fry the actual boss?
Wow, that's interesting. Yoshi even kept the springboard in his mouth during the blast off! That doesn't happen in the original game!
Oh, yeah. Gotta check every pipe, because you never know with this game...
Man, these wider jumps keep worrying me, due to how I slow down in midair.
Hmm... I don't think I need the springboard to reach that midpoint!
Umm... I don't think she's coming back...
Umm... I just thought of something... How will this game handle/replace the pipe cannons that should be in this level?
Wow, I wonder if the programmers deemed the original setups (with spikes on both sides of the Thwomps) too difficult with this game's physics...
And now for the same exact thing again!
Let's see... Cape spins work on Ninjis...
To be continued...
Oof! Got hit there, but it was still a non-important situation, so I'm fine.
Wow, it felt like I barely made that jump.
Okay, here's where I should be able to power back up, but getting past this Thwomp will be tricky...
Umm... I don't think I'm going for those coins...
It is indeed Wendy, although with Lemmy's room setup. And what's this? I'm able to fry stuff in here!
Midpoint! Okay, now the next room's got Thwomps, right?
Oh, wow! The pipe cannon actually worked properly! Given what I've seen so far, I'm actually a little surprised when I see anything slightly fancy like that working correctly in this game!
Ooh, nice! I did that part perfectly! Now to fully power up!
Oh, it's actually Chocolate Island 1! And I guess this game can handle Dino Rhinos!
However, knowing this game's physics, maybe I can trigger it from the side with the springboard's help?
D'oh! I got killed because of standing small Mario's oversized hitbox!
Yeah, the small ones can be fried alright, but the hit detection on my shots hitting them seems weird.
Yep.
Hmm... You know what? I think I'll hang onto my flower. I want to see if anything in the boss's room will be flammable or inflammable!
Wow, those Dino Rhinos are really spazzing out. I'd better be careful!
Well, let's try that again...
Whoa, that thing's fast! I should've tried going over it instead.
Demo count: 17
...but fireballs don't, even though they do in the original game.
Hi, Yoshi! Hi briefly floating springboard!
Oh, and once again, the Thwimps got replaced with Ninjis.
Alright, time for the next level. I'm guessing it'll be Chocolate Island 3.
Oh, that was actually no problem!
Well, Yoshi might make this area slightly easier. But only slightly, because I doubt he can bounce off of the Thwomps, and I have no idea if he can safely stand on spikes.
Once again, I'm holding off using my reserve item, because I'm expecting another power up shortly.
Pencils? Oh, so this is Chocolate Fortress, eh? (Also, pencils seem slightly fancy, so yay for them being here!)

It doesn't look like the screen scrolls up here, so no cloudy ledge with a moon like in the original... (In fact, I haven't seen any moons in this game yet, not even in a couple of their expected locations.)
